sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Testing construct. GFP expression is controlled by arabinose and theophylline via the pBAD promoter and the theophylline riboswitch.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amy Soon
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: pBAD and GFP are from the iGEM distribution kit plates and the riboswitch is from the Gallivan Lab's paper A flow cytometry-based screen for synthetic riboswitches. by Lynch et al. in Appl Environ Microbiol.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The end of the riboswitch sequence must be directly before the start codon of the coding sequence for GFP. There cannot be a scar.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1212000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Codes for an RNA secondary structure that, in the presence of theophylline, undergoes a conformational change that makes the previously sequestered ribosome binding site available for binding thus allowing for transcription of the downstream sequence. Nominal induction levels for theophylline are 0 to 10 mM. Achieves an 59 - fold activation ratio in 1 mM theophylline as reported by Gallivan and Lynch in 'A flow cytometry based screen for synthetic riboswitches.' Nucleic Acids Res. 2009 January; 37(1): 184???192.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aura Ferreiro
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Nucleic Acids Res. 2009 January; 37(1): 184???192. Synthetic riboswitch screened from a library of randomized mutants created by cloning theophylline aptamers upstream of the RBS of a B-galactosidase reporter gene where the distance between the aptamer and the RBS was variable.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pBAD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pBAD is an E.coli promoter that is induced by L-arabinose. K206000 is a mutagenized pBAD promoter that is responsive to lower concentrations of arabinose than wild type (I13453) and, additionally, exhibits a higher maximum of protein expression as measured by coupling to a fluorescent reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amelia Hardjasa
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was obtained by applying all mutations that upregulated AraC binding and subsequent promoter activity listed in reference [1].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special design considerations.
